commit.message: Added FreeBSD CI support

Adapt tests to improve BSD support (#633)

* Adapt tests to improve BSD support.

There was a false Linux|Windows dichotomy in some tests, so instead of
skipping certain tests on certain platforms, this now skips tests when
*not* on the expected platform.
E.g. InotifyFullEmitter tests shouldn't run on non-Linux and the
Windows-specific tests shouldn't run on non-Windows.

* Revert change to `test_separate_consecutive_moves`.

That way CI is happy and changes are conceptually more isolated.

commit.message:
Fixed the build_ext command on macOS Catalina

Added `-Wno-nullability-extension` and `-Wno-newline-eof`
to compilation arguments.

Refactor FileSystemEventHandler.dispatch()

And simplify `dispatch()` methdod of `PatternMatchingEventHandler`
and `RegexMatchingEventHandler`.

Bump the version to 0.10.2

Also set the full range copyright years and
mention the project is healthy thanks to all
contributors.
Release 0.10.1
[mac] add -Wno-nullability-completeness to compilation arguments

Fix macOS build_ext for old and new versions

- Removed old C code for Python 2.5
- Fixed error: equality comparison with extraneous parentheses
- Removed use of `distuils.util.get_platform()` for `sys.platform` in `setup.py`
- Removed `-Werror` to fix several issues when compiling the extension
- Moved requirements to `setup.cfg`

Add LC_ALL=C to Python 3.6 test on GNU/Linux

And correct the changelog + documentation.

Fix Python 3.6 installation when the OS locale is set to POSIX (#616)

* enforce 'utf-8' encoding, fixes #615

* using `open` from `codecs` for py2.7 support

* Updated changelog to reflect OS locale fix
Update v0.10.0 release date in changelog.rst
Merge branch 'v0.10.x'

Fix two changelog titles to push to PyPI

These subtitles in the v0.10.0 section were blocking the upload of
the new release
